{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 180°C. Line 2 baking trays with baking paper and set aside.","Place white sugar into mixing bowl and mill <nobr>4 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Place 30 g of the pistachio nuts into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Place remaining pistachio nuts and 30 g of the reserved sugar into mixing bowl and mill <nobr>15 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>.","Add rice flour and mix <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside. Throughly clean and dry mixing bowl."," <strong>Insert<\/strong> <strong>butterfly<\/strong> <strong>whisk<\/strong> <strong>.<\/strong> Place egg whites into mixing bowl and whisk <nobr>2 min\/37°C\/speed 3.5<\/nobr>.","With butterfly whisk still in place, whip <nobr>3 min\/37°C\/speed 3<\/nobr>, slowly add remaining reserved sugar through hole in mixing bowl lid, 1 spoon at a time, until soft peaks form and meringue is glossy. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add vanilla and reserved pistachio and sugar mixture and combine <nobr>4 sec\/\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then repeat <nobr>4 sec\/\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Place a teaspoonful of biscuit mixture onto 1 of the prepared baking trays, then top with a sprinkle of the reserved crushed pistachios. Repeat with remaining biscuit mixture to form approx. 20 biscuits and garnish with remaining crushed pistachio nuts.","Bake for 9 minutes (180°C) or until browned around the edges. Dust with pure icing sugar while still warm, then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely (approx. 20 minutes) before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["80 g white sugar","90 g pistachio nuts","30 g rice flour","2 egg whites","1 tsp natural vanilla extract","2 tbsp pure icing sugar, for dusting"]}],"id":"r77147","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-GVmLhyZOoko\/XZau4h0bxUI\/AAAAAAAAhoM\/DQyc9jenTZU2